3. The joint probability mass function of two discrete random variables $X$ and $Y$ is given by $p(x, y)=c x y$ for $x=1,2,3$ and $y=1,2,3$, and zero otherwise. Find
(a) the constant $c$;
(d) $\mathrm{P}(X \geq 2)$;
(g) $\mathrm{P}(Y=3)$.
(b) $\mathrm{P}(X=2, Y=3)$;
(e) $\mathrm{P}(Y<2)$;
(c) $\mathrm{P}(X \leq 2, Y \leq 2)$;
(f) $\mathrm{P}(X=1)$;

4. Let $X$ and $Y$ be continuous random variables having joint density function $f(x, y)=c\left(x^{2}+y^{2}\right)$ when $0 \leq x \leq 1$ and $0 \leq y \leq 1$, and $f(x, y)=0$ otherwise. Determine
(a) the constant $c$;
(d) $\mathrm{P}(Y<1 / 2)$;
(b) $\mathrm{P}(X<1 / 2, Y>1 / 2)$;
(e) whether $X$ and $Y$ are independent.
(c) $\mathrm{P}(1 / 4<X<3 / 4)$;
